# ECP Specification Rules

- `spec.yaml` is the canonical example ECP Context manifest. Changes MUST keep it valid against `src/schema/ecp-context.schema.ts`.
- After editing `spec.yaml`, run `npm run validate` to verify schema conformance and structural integrity.
- After editing any `.md` file, run `npm run lint:md` to check markdown lint.
- TypeScript types in `src/types/ecp.ts` MUST stay in sync with the spec. If you add a new field to `spec.yaml`, add the corresponding type.
- The JSON Schema in `src/schema/ecp-context.schema.ts` MUST stay in sync with the types and spec.
